738
01:08:51,044 --> 01:08:52,961
-lt's the professor's daughter.
-Really?

739
01:08:53,046 --> 01:08:54,963
That's where he's been living.

740
01:08:59,385 --> 01:09:01,220
Will you come home with me?

741
01:09:02,263 --> 01:09:04,932
-Hey, hey, hey...
-lt's all right. lt's okay.

742
01:09:06,267 --> 01:09:08,894
-Come on. Come on.
-Let's go, buddy.

743
01:09:08,978 --> 01:09:10,854
-Thank you very much.
-Okay.

744
01:09:10,939 --> 01:09:12,397
Thank you!

745
01:09:17,904 --> 01:09:19,488
That's the best thing.

746
01:09:20,573 --> 01:09:22,324
Come on, give me a coffee.

747
01:09:23,660 --> 01:09:25,702
Jasjeet, come on. Give me a coffee.

748
01:09:39,759 --> 01:09:43,512
l think of him, too. Every day.

749
01:10:11,791 --> 01:10:13,125
Hey.

750
01:10:14,544 --> 01:10:16,420
You know we love you, Hachi.

751
01:10:17,380 --> 01:10:19,631
We want you to stay here with us.

752
01:10:23,177 --> 01:10:27,848
But if you have to go, that's okay, too.

753
01:10:29,726 --> 01:10:30,934
Okay.

754
01:10:50,163 --> 01:10:51,538
Goodbye, Hachi.

755
01:11:04,093 --> 01:11:06,011
Good afternoon, Hachi.

756
01:11:36,250 --> 01:11:38,001
Hey, Hachi.

757
01:11:38,878 --> 01:11:41,922
Here you go. Don't tell Myra, all right?

758
01:11:44,509 --> 01:11:46,385
Good night, Hachi.

759
01:12:12,912 --> 01:12:15,831
-Hello, how are you?
-l think...

760
01:12:32,306 --> 01:12:34,766
Lucky! Let's go.

761
01:12:34,851 --> 01:12:36,768
Come on, sweetie. Hey, Lucky.

762
01:12:38,604 --> 01:12:40,772
Hey, girl. Come on, Lucky, let's go.

763
01:12:47,780 --> 01:12:50,032
Hey, excuse me, sir.

764
01:12:50,116 --> 01:12:52,743
-The dog out there.
-Yeah?

765
01:12:52,827 --> 01:12:55,954
ls that the dog that l've been hearing
so much about?

766
01:12:58,583 --> 01:13:00,375
What's it to you?

767
01:13:00,460 --> 01:13:04,921
l'm sorry. l'm Teddy Barnes.
l'm with the Woonsocket CaII.

768
01:13:06,966 --> 01:13:09,217
Yeah, l've been hearing a lot of talk
about him on the trains.

769
01:13:09,302 --> 01:13:12,304
l don't know,
sounds like it could make a good story.

770
01:13:15,349 --> 01:13:18,060
lt's Boilins, Carl Boilins.

771
01:13:18,144 --> 01:13:22,564
B-O-l-L-l-N-S. Yes. There's no "Y" in there.

772
01:13:22,648 --> 01:13:25,067
l'm the one that found him,
handed him over.

773
01:13:25,151 --> 01:13:26,610
Yeah?

774
01:13:26,694 --> 01:13:31,156
So, Carl, where's he live?

775
01:13:31,240 --> 01:13:35,660
Well, we're not really sure.
He comes and goes.

776
01:13:36,454 --> 01:13:39,873
-Nobody bothers him?
-No, we put up with him.

777
01:13:39,957 --> 01:13:42,250
He just does what he's doing.

778
01:13:42,335 --> 01:13:44,920
Hey, you mind if l take a picture?

779
01:13:45,713 --> 01:13:48,590
-For the newspaper.
-l don't mind if Hachi don't mind.

780
01:13:48,674 --> 01:13:52,052
Thank you very much. Very nice, very nice.

781
01:13:52,136 --> 01:13:54,262
One without first, please.

782
01:13:54,347 --> 01:13:56,765
Without the dog? All right. Stay there.

783
01:13:57,892 --> 01:13:59,559
Well, l...

784
01:14:00,978 --> 01:14:03,271
-Yeah. All right.
-l appreciate it.

785
01:14:03,356 --> 01:14:05,190
That's very kind of you.

786
01:14:07,235 --> 01:14:08,443
-Okay, nice and tight.
-Yeah.

787
01:14:08,528 --> 01:14:10,112
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

788
01:14:10,196 --> 01:14:11,196
Look at that there.

789
01:14:11,280 --> 01:14:12,572
Big smile.

790
01:14:13,449 --> 01:14:17,285
That's... That's beautiful. Thank you.

791
01:14:31,551 --> 01:14:33,051
Hey, Hachi.

792
01:14:34,804 --> 01:14:38,640
This kid in Derry sent you his lunch money.

793
01:14:39,433 --> 01:14:41,726
He wants me to buy you treats with it.

794
01:14:42,770 --> 01:14:44,771
lt's like the third one this week.

795
01:14:44,856 --> 01:14:48,692
lf this keeps up,
l'll have to open a bank account for you.

796
01:14:49,610 --> 01:14:51,736
Don't say l never gave you nothing.

797
01:14:54,407 --> 01:14:56,825
The dog's making out like a bandit here.

798
01:14:57,201 --> 01:14:59,286
Look at this, isn't that cute?

799
01:15:01,289 --> 01:15:02,455
Hey, Hach.

800
01:15:03,040 --> 01:15:05,167
-What are you doing with the money?
-l'm his executor.

801
01:15:15,595 --> 01:15:17,429
Be right with you, sir.

802
01:15:18,764 --> 01:15:23,143
<i>River Junction local is now boarding</i>
<i>on track two, it's making all stops.</i>

803
01:15:33,070 --> 01:15:34,446
Hachi.

804
01:15:39,327 --> 01:15:41,244
Here you go, Hachi.

805
01:15:41,954 --> 01:15:43,371
There you are.

806
01:15:44,081 --> 01:15:45,207
Hungry, huh?

807
01:15:45,833 --> 01:15:48,919
Yes, he's very cold. He must eat.

808
01:15:51,047 --> 01:15:53,715
l'm Jasjeet. l run the hot dog stand.

809
01:15:53,925 --> 01:15:56,509
l'm Ken Fujiyoshi,
Professor Wilson's friend.

810
01:15:56,594 --> 01:15:58,345
Mr. Professor?

811
01:15:59,555 --> 01:16:01,097
One sugar, two cream.

812
01:16:02,767 --> 01:16:04,601
So then you must have read
the article, then?

813
01:16:04,685 --> 01:16:07,062
-l did.
-You saw my name in the article?

814
01:16:08,439 --> 01:16:11,149
-Yes, l did.
-Twice.

815
01:16:11,234 --> 01:16:13,235
Please, let me help with the expense.

816
01:16:13,319 --> 01:16:17,447
-No, no, no, please. No money.
-What if he gets sick? Medical expenses?

817
01:16:17,531 --> 01:16:19,407
We'll take a collection.

818
01:16:19,492 --> 01:16:24,079
From the travelers, the vendors,
and we will take care of it for him.

819
01:16:24,163 --> 01:16:26,164
The station square is Hachi's home now.

820
01:16:26,249 --> 01:16:29,584
Every day he comes,
same time, same place, here only.

821
01:16:29,669 --> 01:16:32,879
-You'll do that for him?
-Take care of him?

822
01:16:32,964 --> 01:16:34,297
Of course.

823
01:16:36,550 --> 01:16:38,051
All right, then l...

824
01:16:38,886 --> 01:16:41,638
l've got to sell some hot dogs.
Good to meet you.

825
01:16:41,722 --> 01:16:44,266
You, too. Thank you very much.

826
01:16:48,437 --> 01:16:49,729
lt's been a year, hasn't it?

827
01:16:52,692 --> 01:16:55,193
l wake up sometimes
in the middle of the night

828
01:16:55,444 --> 01:16:58,196
and think about Parker.
He was a good friend.

829
01:16:59,073 --> 01:17:01,950
l understand how you feel.

830
01:17:03,119 --> 01:17:06,204
Hachi, my friend,
Parker is never coming home.

831
01:17:06,706 --> 01:17:09,874
But if Hachiko wants to wait,
then Hachiko should wait.

832
01:17:10,042 --> 01:17:13,420
You want to wait for him, don't you?

833
01:17:16,382 --> 01:17:20,427
Have a long life Hachi.

834
01:17:31,439 --> 01:17:36,901
Come on, mister. There we are.
That's a good boy.

835
01:17:41,073 --> 01:17:44,242
Want some more? Okay, come on.

836
01:17:47,204 --> 01:17:51,833
Okay, come on, boy. Last piece.
lt's good, huh?

837
01:18:04,972 --> 01:18:06,806
See you tomorrow, Hachi.

838
01:18:08,559 --> 01:18:09,768
Ciao, Hachi.

839
01:18:46,055 --> 01:18:51,393
<i>Final call for Oakland, Wood River Junction</i>
<i>and Four Corners</i>

840
01:18:51,477 --> 01:18:53,186
<i>leaving from track two.</i>

841
01:19:11,205 --> 01:19:13,581
Ms. Wilson? Nice to see you again.

842
01:19:13,666 --> 01:19:15,458
-Good afternoon.
-Thank you.

843
01:19:16,919 --> 01:19:19,003
That's the professor's wife, huh?

844
01:20:19,565 --> 01:20:20,732
Cate.

845
01:20:24,862 --> 01:20:25,987
Ken.

846
01:20:29,074 --> 01:20:30,658
lt's been a while.

847
01:20:31,577 --> 01:20:33,328
lt certainly has.

848
01:20:43,756 --> 01:20:47,509
lt's 1 0 years. Can you believe it?

849
01:21:03,067 --> 01:21:12,534
Hi, Hachi.

850
01:21:31,387 --> 01:21:34,305
-All right, have a good one.
-Thank you, Jas.

851
01:21:41,981 --> 01:21:43,481
-Who would've thought?
-l know.

852
01:21:43,566 --> 01:21:46,025
l mean, when we first went in there,
l was like...

853
01:21:57,663 --> 01:22:07,505
Hachi?

854
01:22:11,510 --> 01:22:14,429
You old thing, you're still waiting.

855
01:22:29,862 --> 01:22:31,404
That's right.

856
01:22:47,671 --> 01:22:51,174
lf it's all right,
could l wait with you for the next train?

857
01:22:54,219 --> 01:22:55,553
Yeah?

858
01:22:57,389 --> 01:22:58,806
Thanks.

859
01:23:08,150 --> 01:23:09,942
Oh, Hachi.

860
01:23:22,748 --> 01:23:24,540
-That's so cute.
-You like that one?

861
01:23:24,625 --> 01:23:26,000
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

862
01:23:26,085 --> 01:23:27,585
That's good, isn't it?

863
01:23:27,670 --> 01:23:30,630
-That's me.
-l know, l remember.

864
01:23:31,340 --> 01:23:34,926
l remember. l was there that day.
l took that picture.

865
01:23:35,844 --> 01:23:37,595
He still looks so cute.

866
01:23:40,140 --> 01:23:42,350
-He went to the wedding.
-Yeah.

867
01:23:42,434 --> 01:23:44,227
He's right there.

868
01:23:45,229 --> 01:23:48,940
-Right there.
-Where did Grandpa find Hachi?

869
01:23:50,150 --> 01:23:53,695
Ronnie, actually,
Hachi found your grandfather.

870
01:23:53,779 --> 01:23:54,862
How?

871
01:23:56,532 --> 01:24:00,952
One night your grandfather
was coming back from a trip.

872
01:24:02,121 --> 01:24:07,792
He got off at the train station,
he went inside of the train station...

873
01:26:03,033 --> 01:26:04,408
Hey, boy.

874
01:26:06,119 --> 01:26:10,081
Hey! Come on, let's go. Come on!

875
01:26:38,110 --> 01:26:39,777
Hachi!

876
01:26:40,195 --> 01:26:41,946
Hey, boy.

877
01:27:24,656 --> 01:27:26,657
<i>l never met my grandfather.</i>

878
01:27:27,492 --> 01:27:29,744
<i>He died when l was just a baby.</i>

879
01:27:29,828 --> 01:27:35,499
But when l hear about him and Hachi,
l feel like l know him.

880
01:27:36,168 --> 01:27:39,170
They taught me the meaning of loyalty,

881
01:27:39,254 --> 01:27:42,840
that you should never forget anyone
that you've loved.

882
01:27:43,634 --> 01:27:47,261
And that's why
Hachi will forever be my hero.

883
01:27:58,148 --> 01:27:59,857
-Oh, my God, look how cute he is!
-Hi, boy.

884
01:27:59,942 --> 01:28:01,567
He drives me crazy.

885
01:28:01,652 --> 01:28:04,028
-Oh, he's happy to see somebody.
-l know.

886
01:28:06,198 --> 01:28:07,740
Can you walk?

887
01:28:11,411 --> 01:28:13,204
Come on, Hachi. Let's go.

888
01:28:16,750 --> 01:28:18,209
Come on.

889
01:28:20,295 --> 01:28:21,963
Hey, here boy.

